# packages/wgpu-wasm/.gitignore — productionised merge of the archived legacy
# wasm-pack shims (naga + rhi-wgpu/crate; both packages were deleted in
# feat-20260511-naga-rhi-wgpu-merge M5 — this single crate replaces both,
# plan-strategy D-P1 + research F-2 / F-3 ship form).
#
# Zero-binary invariant: the compiled `*.wasm` artefact is NOT committed (it
# is the only binary in pkg/). Rebuild it locally / in CI via `build.sh`
# (wasm-pack; needs a Rust toolchain — see CONTRIBUTING §Rust toolchain).
# The pkg/ TEXT glue (.js + .d.ts + package.json + README) IS committed so the
# TS shim consumers (@forgeax/engine-rhi-wgpu + @forgeax/engine-naga) resolve
# `workspace:*` references via pnpm without every contributor running Rust.
# Cargo.lock = application-level crate lock, MUST be checked in (CI cache key =
#              hashFiles(.../Cargo.lock); bundle-size MetricKind cites the
#              resolved wgpu / naga patches from this file).

target/
node_modules/

# The only binary in pkg/: the wasm-pack-compiled module. Rebuilt by build.sh.
pkg/*.wasm
